model.haskell_template:
import Control.Applicative
import Control.Monad
import System.IO


main :: IO ()
main = do
    q_temp <- getLine
    let q = read q_temp :: Int
    forM_ [1..q] $ \a0  -> do
        x_temp <- getLine
        let x = read x_temp :: Int


getMultipleLines :: Int -> IO [String]

getMultipleLines n
    | n <= 0 = return []
    | otherwise = do          
        x <- getLine         
        xs <- getMultipleLines (n-1)    
        let ret = (x:xs)    
        return ret
model.preview: Count the number of non-negative integer a's that are less than some x where the bitwise XOR of a and x is greater than x.
model.clojure_template:
(use '[clojure.string :only (split triml)])

(
        let [
          q_t (read-line) 
          q (Integer/parseInt q_t) 
        ]

      (
        loop [a0 q]
        (when (> a0 0)

          (
            let [
              x_t (read-line) 
              x (Integer/parseInt x_t) 
            ]
          )

        (recur (- a0 1) ) )
      )

)
model.erlang_template:
-module(solution).
-export([main/0]).

main() ->

    { ok, [Q]} = io:fread("", "~d"),
    Q_list = lists:seq(1,Q),
    lists:foreach( fun(Q0) ->
            { ok, [X]} = io:fread("", "~d")
    end,Q_list),
    true.

read_array(0,D) -> [];
read_array(N,D) -> 
	{ok, [X]} = io:fread("", D),
	[X | read_array(N-1,D)].

read_2darray(0,M,D) -> [];
read_2darray(N,M,D) ->
	Q=read_array(M,D),
	[Q | read_2darray(N-1,M,D)].
